'''Du Chengyi''' ({{zh|s=杜成义|t=杜成義|p=Dù Chéngyì}}), known professionally as '''A-do''' (阿杜), is a Singaporean singer .<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/en/doc/2003-11/19/content_282711.htm |title=A-Do-rable singer |publisher=[[China Daily]] |date=19 November 2003 |accessdate=2006-06-13 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5PtmY5sy8?url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/en/doc/2003-11/19/content_282711.htm |archivedate=2007-06-27 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> The ex-[[construction foreman]] was spotted by Singaporean producer Billy Koh in his company's talent search and was signed to Ocean Butterflies Music. He released his debut album in 2002.
