{{Infobox musical artist | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank --> | name = Kay 9ice | caption = | background = solo_singer | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = Philip Kissi | alias = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1990|05|27}} | birth_place = [[Accra]], [[Ghana]] | origin = [[Ghanaian]] | genre = [[Afrobeats]], [[Hiplife]] | occupation = Singer, Songwriter | years_active = 2015–present | label = '''GHOZT MUSIK''' & '''+816 STUDIO''' | associated_acts = | website = <!---{{URL|website}}---> }} '''Philip Kwaku Kissi''' popularly known as '''Kay 9ice''', was born on May 27, 1990 in Accra, Ghana. a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] [[Hiplife]] and [[Afrobeats]] artiste. Kay 9ice currently signed to GHOZT MUSIK<ref>{{cite web | url=http://ezone57.com/get-familiar-kay-9ice-bbc-music-artist/ | title=KAY 9ICE SIGN TO GHOZT MUSIK | publisher= Kofighozt | date= | author= | accessdate=23 August 2018}}</ref> a record label based in [[Ghana]] & +816 studios.
==Biography== Philip hails from Akoefe in the Volta Region of Ghana. Growing up, [[afrobeats]] music became his favorite at the junior high school level Ashaiman Government School. He won himself the pleasure to be the first Ghanaian to be introduced by BBC Music and to feature on BBC6 Music Mixtape.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/introducing/entries/6a33f87e-bbfa-4843-86e2-6f5aa1c6ea86| title=BBC Music Introducing Mixtape 26 March 2018|publisher= Tom Robison | date= | author= | accessdate=23 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kay |first1=9ice |title=Kay 9ice wobeti bbc |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/tracks/n5zpn3 |website=bbc |publisher=Tom Robison |accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref>
Kay 9ice became part of a musical group called Rekx Bois (Real Entertainment Knocked Down Extremely). Due to his hard work musically he had his first big appearance during Flowking Stone's oseikrom shutdown show in Kumasi, Ghana. With his hard work, he got nominated for the median edition for Ashaiman Music Awards 2018 and Ghana Music Awards South Africa for which he got 7 nominations<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kay 9ice |first1=7 nominations |title=Kay 9ice 7 nominations |agency=ModernGhana |ref=https://www.modernghana.com/entertainment/52027/kay-9ice-bags-7-nominations-at-the-maiden-amas.html}}</ref> and promising Artist Of The Year 2018<ref>{{cite news |last1=2018 Ghana Music Awards South Africa: Check |first1=The Full List of Nominees |title=2018 Ghana Music Awards South Africa: Check The Full List of Nominees |agency=NYDJ live |ref=https://www.nydjlive.com/2018-ghana-music-awards-south-africa-check-the-full-list-of-nominees/}}</ref> respectively.
== Achievement == He won the Afro-Song Of The Year category in The median edition Of the Ashaiman Music Awards 2018 and was also nominated for ghana Music awards south africa. He is also the first ghanaian to be feature on BBC 6 Music Introducing Mixtape.
